The Caretaker/Extra-Ordinary National Convention Planning Committee of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has commenced preparation for the Ondo State governorship poll. The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) had fixed the election for October 10, 2020. On Monday, APC named ex-interim National Secretary, Tijjani Musa Tumsa to chair the committee to screen Ondo governorship aspirants. Umar Lawan-Kareto will chair the screening appeal committee. Full list of members below: Screening Committee
Tijjani Musa Tumsa (Chairman)
Solomon Johnny
Abayomi Oyalowo
Princess Gloria Akumbomdu
Rt. Hon. Eugine Udo
Barr. Usman Dalhatu
Amb. Fati Bala
Prof. Okay Onyejekwe
Prof. Shehu Adamaraji (Secretary) Appeal Committee
Umar Lawan-Kareto (Chairman)
Hon. Ibrahim Ebbo
Maj. Gen. Christian O. Ogwo (rtd.)
Alh. Danladi Chambas, Imabong Ubo
Barr. Odeh Sam
Prof. Mojeed Alabi
Rt. Hon. Opeyemi Ajayi
Senator Andrew Uchendu (*Secretary*) The committees will be inaugurated at the APC national secretariat on Tuesday 7th July, 2020 by 2pm.